    {
      "id": 246424,
      "postNumber": 4,
      "createdAt": "2026-02-24T07:52:05.929Z",
      "author": "YOGESHP (Yogesh Pokale)",
      "cookedHtml": "<p>Hi <a class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/zohreh\">@zohreh</a>, welcome to the community! <img src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/apple/waving_hand.png?v=15\" title=\":waving_hand:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":waving_hand:\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" /></p>\n<p>You can do this using a Formula column. If your Hour columns are named Hour 1 and Hour 2, use:</p>\n<p>{Hour 1} - {Hour 2}</p>\n<p>This will subtract Hour 1 from Hour 2 and return the result in the formula column.</p>\n<p>And if you’d like to display Hr / Hrs after the value, you can use:</p>\n<p>IF({Hour 1} - {Hour 2} &lt; 10, CONCATENATE({Hour 1} - {Hour 2}, \" Hr\"), CONCATENATE({Hour 1} - {Hour 2}, \" Hrs\"))</p>\n<p>Hope this helps!!</p>"
    },
